Haemodialysis Staff Nurse
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/04 16:14:05
Ref. JB3047200
Job Description
On behalf of our client one of the leading Specialist Hospitals in Saudi Arabia we have an opening for a Haemodialysis Staff Nurse.
Reporting to the Head Nurse you will provide a comprehensive care and treatments to acute and chronic haemodialysis
patients and care to the unit and haemodialysis machines
Duties & Responsibilities
•	Prepare the haemodialysis machine with all equipments needed prior to dialysis sessions.
•	Assess, plan and carries out individualized comprehensive care to the patients, taking into account the physical, psychological and cultural background.
•	Prepares, administers and charts all medication in medication sheet.
•	Understands the therapeutic effects of medication, dosages, contra-indications and adverse reaction of these drugs.
•	Maintains accountability and accuracy of narcotic and control drugs.
•	Familiar with all emergency operational procedures including machine malfunction during dialysis, this involves knowledge of the back-up system for returning patients blood should pump failure occur.
•	Able to safely and efficiently operate a variety of haemodialysis machines used in the unit, this includes knowledge and proficiency in handling all of the equipment used on the machines.
•	Assessment of AV access, cannulation of AV fistulas or AV grafts which require skill in venipuncture.
•	Sets up equipment and assists physician with insertion of double lumen femoral catheters.
•	Records on patient flow sheet any reactions and the progress of patients during dialysis treatment.
•	Recognizes any abnormal changes in patient condition and takes appropriate lifesaving measures.
•	Seeks advice from dietary and social services for any problems raised regarding patient in end stage renal disease.
•	Participates effectively in nursing meetings, education, and infection control and quality improvements activities.
•	Participates in patient and family education; call patient educator when needed.
•	Perform other applicable task and duties assigned with the realm of his/her knowledge skills and duties.
•	Obtains and documents patient’s pre-dialysis vital signs, weight and patient’s physical assessment.
•	Inspects and documents patient’s dialysis access.
•	Administers anticoagulant according to unit protocols and prescription.
•	Adjust blood flow rates according to established protocols and prescription.
•	Calculates and adjusts fluid removal rates according to patient’s weight gain.
•	Monitors patients and equipment, every 30 minutes, respond to alarm and readjust treatment parameters.
•	Responds appropriately to dialysis related emergencies such as hypotensive episodes, needle displacement or infiltration, clotting episodes, blood leaks, bleeding, air emboli, etc.
•	Records post dialysis vital signs, temperature, weight and access status.
•	Participates actively with primary patients care.
Skills
•	Specialty Qualifications/ Professional Experience
•	Baccalaureate degree in Nursing/ Diploma in Nursing.
•	Graduate from recognized college of nursing.
•	Registration in country of origin.
•	MOH License to work in KSA
•	2 years’ experience after graduation.
•	Training experience in Hemodialysis
•	Knowledge of English and Arabic preferred.
•	Computer literate.
•	ACLS & BCLS licensed.
